cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CE

This paper deals with the analysis of user behavior in digital games using telemetry data, which involves the use of machine learning techniques to cluster player behavior. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically deals with the application of unsupervised clustering techniques to behavioral data. Additionally, the paper discusses the development of actionable behavioral profiles, which could fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of Archetypal Analysis, a technique for identifying extreme or prototypical observations in a dataset, could also fall under the category of computational engineering, simulation, and optimization (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of a large dataset over a long period of time, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
